gmd:description.gco:CharacterString:
All  NUTS 2003 feature classes were based on common repository coverages. These are collections of geometry from different sources which contain all geometry necessary to created the different feature classes for the datasets COMM, NUTS, CNTR and HYDR. The creation of the common repository coverage is a complex process with a lot of manual handling. Here only the process steps after the creation of the common repository are briefly described:


Step 1: The first step was to create an empty database schema for the NUTS_2003 dataset;


Step 2: Pre-processing coverage data to prepare them to load into the new Geodatabase structure which included: 
       (i) clean coverages with correct precision + check for labelerrors;
       (ii) creating regions for each NUTS level (to match subtypes in the GDB);
       (iii) deriving tables that define relationship between boundaries and regions;
       (iv) attribute manipulation to match the new structure;
       (v) converting NUTS attribute table with correct encoding type (UTF8) for database loading.


Step 3: the preprocessed coverages were loaded in the empty geodatabase schema for the NUTS_2003 dataset;


Step 4: adding metadata
